From: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Date: Tue, 28 Oct 2014 12:42:19 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: pcm: Zero-clear reserved fields of PCM status ioctl in compat mode
Git-commit: 317168d0c766defd14b3d0e9c2c4a9a258b803ee
Patch-mainline: 3.18-rc4
References: boo#916608

In compat mode, we copy each field of snd_pcm_status struct but don't
touch the reserved fields, and this leaves uninitialized values
there.  Meanwhile the native ioctl does zero-clear the whole
structure, so we should follow the same rule in compat mode, too.

Reported-by: Pierre-Louis Bossart <pierre-louis.bossart@linux.intel.com>
Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

